					<description><![CDATA[<p>Fund II Surpasses Expectations NOVA Infrastructure announced the final close of NOVA Fund II at $1.45 billion. The total exceeded the original target by over 30%. It also more than</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/nova-raises-1-45b-for-north-american-infrastructure-investments/" data-wpel-link="internal">NOVA Raises $1.45B for North American Infrastructure Investments</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Fund II Surpasses Expectations</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">NOVA Infrastructure announced the final close of NOVA Fund II at $1.45 billion. The total exceeded the original target by over 30%. It also more than doubled the amount raised in NOVA Fund I, which closed in 2022.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Chris Beall, the founder and managing partner, said that the fund’s oversubscription shows just how confident investors are in NOVA’s investment strategy. Investors from Fund I came back for this round, and they were joined by new backers from North America, Europe, Asia, and the Middle East.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The fund sticks with NOVA’s approach: targeting middle-market investments where there’s room to add real value. It targets operational businesses in energy, energy transition, digital infrastructure, transportation, and environmental services.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">NOVA Fund II is structured to emphasise downside protection while creating operational improvements. Every investment gets a close look for quick results and long-term growth. Beall pointed out that investors really cared about both angles. </span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Lazard took charge as the placement agent for the fund, and Jones Day handled the legal side, making sure everything was set up and offered correctly around the world. Thanks to these collaborations, Fund II stayed on track with international rules and brought in a wide mix of investors.</span></p>
<h2><b>Early Platform Investments</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Fund II is off to a running start, with two platform investments already under its belt. DartPoints manages enterprise data centers that keep cloud computing and digital infrastructure humming. UGE International handles community solar projects and battery storage—so, clean energy that feeds into local power grids.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Both deals show how NOVA does things: they take solid infrastructure businesses and make them better, then build from there. DartPoints keeps data centers up and running, while UGE pushes renewables further into the mainstream. NOVA plans to make 10 to 12 investments like these, focusing mostly on North America.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">That’s where their experience and connections make the biggest impact. They’re zeroing in on sectors that are riding the wave of new technology—think digital infrastructure, data centers, and projects driving the energy transition. There’s a real surge in demand from AI and from the push toward more sustainable energy.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The end goal for NOVA is simple: put together a portfolio of middle-market infrastructure assets that toss off steady cash, but still have room to grow. The fund’s approach is similar to private equity but adapted to infrastructure’s unique risks and returns.</span></p>
<h2><b>Global Investor Support</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_199670" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-199670" class="size-full wp-image-199670" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/NOVA-2.png" alt="A globe with investor connections across continents, accompanied by glowing financial charts." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-199670" class="wp-caption-text">NOVA II secured global investor support from pensions, insurers, and family offices, reinforcing confidence in the firm’s strategy and expanding its market reach. Source: Created by Ventureburn.</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">VA II attracted a broad range of investors. This included pensions, insurance companies, family offices, registered advisers, and consultants. The investor base spans North America, Europe, Asia, and the Middle East.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">US sovereign and pension capital accounted for over half of the commitments. High reup rates from NOVA Fund I reinforced confidence in the strategy. This shows long-term investor trust in the firm’s execution capabilities.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Founder Allison Kingsley highlighted that investor enthusiasm reflected the focus on real assets in the lower mid-market. The combination of operational expertise and sector focus created a compelling story for both returning and new investors.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">NOVA’s investors include organisations with strong expertise in infrastructure, technology, and energy transition. Their involvement allows NOVA to expand its influence and access market opportunities that smaller investors may not reach.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The fund’s geographic diversity also helps mitigate risk. By including investors from multiple regions, NOVA balances exposure to economic fluctuations and creates long-term strategic partnerships.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The confidence from global investors provides NOVA with flexibility. Fund II can support growth initiatives, operational improvements, and strategic acquisitions across the portfolio.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: <a href="https://ventureburn.com/firmus-raises-505m-to-expand-ai-data-centre-infrastructure/" data-wpel-link="internal">Firmus Raises $505M to Expand AI Data Centre Infrastructure</a></span></p>
<h2><b>Infrastructure Strategy in Action</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">NOVA focuses on sectors with durable demand. Energy projects include renewable and transitional energy solutions, while transportation projects cover critical regional logistics. Environmental services investments support water, waste, and </span><a href="https://www.oecd.org/en/publications/understanding-sustainability-initiatives_8f8a3d7f-en.html" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">sustainability initiatives</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400">.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Digital infrastructure has become a key pillar of NOVA’s strategy. Data centres and related assets benefit from rising demand for cloud computing, AI processing, and secure storage solutions. The firm’s early investment in DartPoints reflects this priority.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">NOVA puts money into projects that actually improve the way companies run. That means smarter energy use, new machines, or updating how managers handle things day-to-day. When they do this, the businesses see better cash flow and grow in value over time.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">What sets NOVA apart is its focus on the middle market. Big funds usually skip over these companies, but NOVA sees their solid foundations and real potential. The only thing missing? Enough capital and smart direction—so that&#8217;s what NOVA brings.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Protecting the downside is a big deal for NOVA. Infrastructure usually gives steady returns, but NOVA doesn’t just sit back—they take control with hands-on management and deep knowledge of the industry. They’re picky about what they invest in, and that keeps risks low while boosting profits.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/nova-raises-1-45b-for-north-american-infrastructure-investments/" data-wpel-link="internal">NOVA Raises $1.45B for North American Infrastructure Investments</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
