					<description><![CDATA[<p>E2 Scales Innovation in VTE Treatment Endovascular Engineering, Inc. (“E2”), a commercial-stage medical technology company, announced an oversubscribed $80 million Series C funding round. The financing was co-led by Gilde</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/e2-raises-80m-to-advance-pulmonary-embolism-treatment/" data-wpel-link="internal">E2 Raises $80M to Advance Pulmonary Embolism Treatment</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
