					<description><![CDATA[<p>Indoor Mapping Gap Drives Funding Momentum Mappedin has raised $24.5 million in growth equity to expand its digital indoor mapping platform. The company said the round will support a move</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/mappedin-secures-24-5m-indoor-mapping/" data-wpel-link="internal">Mappedin Secures $24.5M To Expand Indoor Mapping Technology</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>Indoor Mapping Gap Drives Funding Momentum</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Mappedin has raised $24.5 million in growth equity to expand its digital indoor mapping platform. The company said the round will support a move from building-level mapping to large-scale deployments that cover entire districts and public environments.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Most outdoor areas have been fully mapped. Indoor spaces remain fragmented due to constant changes and private ownership. Many buildings rely on static floor plans that fail to reflect real-time conditions. Mappedin aims to change this through an AI-driven platform that creates live, 3D maps of complex environments.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company uses artificial intelligence and LiDAR to update indoor spaces in real time. This gives teams a dynamic operational layer that supports navigation, safety, and intelligence. It also helps organisations coordinate operations more effectively across large and complex venues.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Mappedin said customer needs have expanded. What started as basic navigation support is now used for operations, security, and emergency coordination. The company believes its platform can improve visitor experiences at public venues and support critical response efforts.</span></p>
<h2><b>Spatial Technology Extends Inside Public Venues</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The new capital expands access to indoor mapping tools for public spaces. These include airports, large venues, retail centres, and stadiums. Indoor mapping is becoming important as buildings turn into dynamic environments that require fast updates. Many teams still rely on separate systems that do not interact. This slows down planning and response.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Mappedin wants to unify this information. The platform lets operators create and maintain 3D maps that support multiple functions. Navigation improves as users move through large spaces. Operations teams gain insight into layouts. Safety teams can access live maps during critical events.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company said indoor mapping is essential for large destinations that handle significant foot traffic. Digital updates help teams understand how visitors move. They also support maintenance planning and risk assessment. These capabilities gain value as venues grow more complex.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The new funding supports the company’s expansion into city-scale deployments. These deployments could provide indoor coverage for multi-building districts. The company believes this will become part of broader digital infrastructure.</span></p>
<h2><b>Growth Strategy Focuses on Scale and Intelligence<br />
</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_199647" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-199647" class="size-full wp-image-199647" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/a-futuristic-neon-lit-poster-showcasing-_nAdoCnSYT5iGCJqP3RDZLQ_xQ4FJPq9S-iazG6a9szm8w.png" alt="Real-time indoor mapping system using AI and LiDAR for navigation and emergency response." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-199647" class="wp-caption-text">Illustration of Mappedin’s live indoor mapping platform supporting operations, safety, and real-time decision-making. Source: Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Mappedin plans to invest the new capital into platform development and customer growth. The company said it will build more tools to support operations, analytics, and safety. These tools help organisations see real-time conditions in indoor environments. This allows teams to respond faster and work with more accuracy.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Indoor mapping presents unique challenges. Spaces change often. Fixtures move. Rooms shift. Traditional mapping cannot keep up. The company’s use of AI and LiDAR helps solve this problem. These technologies capture detailed </span><a href="https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/spatial" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">spatial</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> information quickly. They also update maps without requiring manual redesign.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company also plans to expand its support for first responders. Live maps give emergency teams a clearer understanding of building layouts. This helps them plan routes, respond to incidents, and coordinate actions. Digital maps can support time-critical decisions.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company’s growth aligns with rising demand for indoor spatial intelligence. More organisations want tools that deliver a unified view of operations. Mappedin aims to be the core layer powering this shift.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: <a href="https://ventureburn.com/modus-raises-85m-ai-audit-technology/" data-wpel-link="internal">Modus Raises $85M To Advance AI Audit Technology</a></span></p>
<h2><b>Indoor Digital Infrastructure Gains Enterprise Adoption</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company said that adoption is growing among organisations that manage large indoor environments. These include malls, airports, and entertainment venues. Many of these environments have millions of square feet. Managing them requires accurate spatial data. The company’s platform has already mapped billions of square feet across multiple regions.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Mappedin sees itself as a foundational platform for indoor digital infrastructure. It aims to support systems that depend on reliable spatial information. These include navigation apps, security tools, analytics platforms, and operations dashboards. When all these tools run from one mapping layer, accuracy improves across the board.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Indoor spaces will continue to change. This creates a need for technology that can adapt fast. The company believes its system meets this need by linking advanced mapping with operational intelligence. The funding round strengthens its ability to serve global customers.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">A recent study on indoor mapping highlighted how critical indoor coverage has become. It noted that indoor areas represent a significant portion of daily human movement. The study also emphasised that safety, operations, and navigation benefit from precise maps.</span></p>
