					<description><![CDATA[<p>AI Audit Model Gains Pace Modus has secured $85 million in new funding to expand its audit-focused technology platform. The company said the raise includes a seed round and a</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/modus-raises-85m-ai-audit-technology/" data-wpel-link="internal">Modus Raises $85M To Advance AI Audit Technology</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2><b>AI Audit Model Gains Pace</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Modus has secured $85 million in new funding to expand its audit-focused technology platform. The company said the raise includes a seed round and a Series A round. The goal is to strengthen its AI-native audit tools and invest in accounting firms that want to modernise their workflows.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company uses </span><a href="https://www.britannica.com/technology/artificial-intelligence" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener external noreferrer" data-wpel-link="external"><span style="font-weight: 400">artificial intelligence</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> to streamline audit tasks. It also works with accounting firms through a partnership-led strategy that preserves firm identity and client relationships. Modus said it wants to help teams deliver higher quality audits through advanced automation.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The funding round was led by a major venture investor with support from other backers. The firm said the capital will accelerate development of its audit tooling. It will also support majority stake acquisitions in advisory entities linked to accounting firms. This structure allows the company to support partners without interfering in firm governance.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company launched last year and has already shown strong traction. It made its first investment in a regional accounting platform with more than $30 million in revenue. That firm is expected to double its organic growth rate by 2026 after adopting Modus’s tools.</span></p>
<h2><b>Audit Processes Undergo Shift</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Audit work depends on accuracy and consistency. Many firms still rely on outdated tools that slow teams down. Modus believes this gap creates room for technology-led solutions. Its platform uses agents to manage tasks that often consume auditor time. These include collecting client data, standardising financial documents, testing controls, and preparing workpapers.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Each step links back to source documents. This ensures traceability. It also gives auditors a clear view of evidence. Modus said this transparency is central to its approach. The company’s leaders argued that trust is essential in the audit field. They said firms must maintain quality even as they adopt new tools.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company sees its model as distinct from traditional investment firms. While it takes majority stakes in advisory entities, it does not direct firm operations. Its goal is to give firms access to technology and capital. The model functions as a support system rather than a takeover. Modus said this approach helps firms scale while keeping their culture intact.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Partner firms benefit from shared technology, shared support, and shared expertise. The company said that its partners report improved efficiency and more time for judgment-heavy work. This aligns with the firm’s long-term aim to modernise audit processes without losing the discipline the field requires.</span></p>
<h2><b>Investment Strategy Supports Growth<br />
</b></h2>
<div id="attachment_199639" style="width: 1322px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-199639" class="size-full wp-image-199639" src="https://ventureburn.com/wp-content/uploads/2026/04/a-futuristic-neon-lit-poster-showcasing-_XJpGFa0hQP-TgAp7SEh9kA_fwW_O0j9SpSkuASPfs62kw_cover.png" alt="AI-powered audit system streamlining workflows across multiple firms and industries." width="1312" height="736" /><p id="caption-attachment-199639" class="wp-caption-text">Illustration of Modus scaling audit technology with AI-driven efficiency and firm-ted by wide integration. Source: Created by Ventureburn</p></div>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Most of the new capital is allocated for acquisitions and follow-on deals. The company plans to make at least five new investments this year. A portion of the funding will also expand the engineering team. Modus said engineering growth is needed to scale its tools. These tools support firms that work with complex clients across multiple industries.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company wants to address a gap in the market. Technology adoption in public accounting has lagged behind other sectors. Many firms still operate fragmented systems that slow audit delivery. Modus said it can change this with a product-first philosophy. The focus is to create technology that fits audit needs rather than generic tools.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Modus uses artificial intelligence to support procedures that require structure and precision. It also builds review flows that help auditors understand each step of the process. The company said this reduces the risk of errors. It also helps teams focus on decisions that require human judgment.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The company’s leaders said the audit field has not changed meaningfully in decades. They believe this provides an opportunity for platforms designed for audit quality and efficiency. Modus aims to build a nationwide system of partner firms using the same technology. This system will support consistency and scale.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">More News: </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/xoople-raises-130m-to-build-global-system-of-record-for-physical-change/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">Xoople Raises $130M to Build Global System of Record for Physical Change</span></a></p>
<h2><b>AI Adoption Brings Competitive Advantage</b></h2>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">The new funding helps Modus position itself as a central player in audit transformation. The company said that firms adopting its tools gain an advantage. They can deliver work faster while maintaining quality. They can also improve risk assessment with stronger data flows. This helps firms compete as client demands increase.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Modus plans to keep investing in its technology stack. It expects to expand product capabilities across data intake, testing, and review functions. The company said these improvements will support firms that manage complex engagements. It also noted that its model works well in sectors that need strong regulatory discipline.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">Its leadership team includes professionals from major technology and investment firms. It also works with advisers who have experience in audit oversight and firm growth. This mix of expertise allows Modus to balance innovation with regulatory expectations. The company believes this balance will shape the next phase of audit technology.</span></p>
<p><span style="font-weight: 400">To stay updated on crypto venture capital funding and market trends, visit our </span><a href="https://ventureburn.com/category/news/venture-capital/" data-wpel-link="internal"><span style="font-weight: 400">venture capital news section</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400"> for more insights.</span></p>
<p>The post <a href="https://ventureburn.com/modus-raises-85m-ai-audit-technology/" data-wpel-link="internal">Modus Raises $85M To Advance AI Audit Technology</a> appeared first on <a href="https://ventureburn.com" data-wpel-link="internal">Ventureburn</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
